HEADWORD: Quadripartition
<hw>Quad`ri*par*ti"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>quadripartitio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>quadripartition</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A division or distribution by four, or into four parts; also, a
taking the fourth part of any quantity or number.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quadripennate</ent>⟦br⟧
